Drop your Google service-account JSON file here, named `gcp-sa.json`.

The same SA powers GA4, GSC, and GTM in the broker. Steps:

1. Google Cloud Console → IAM & Admin → Service Accounts → Create
   - Name: clau-broker-<project>
   - Role: leave blank (we grant access per-product, not via IAM)
2. On the new SA → Keys → Add Key → Create new key → JSON → Download.
3. Save it to this directory as `gcp-sa.json`.
4. Note the SA email, e.g. `clau-broker-foo@my-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com`.
5. Grant access to each product separately:

   GA4:
     analytics.google.com → Admin → Property Access Management
     → Add user → paste SA email → Viewer role.

   GSC (Search Console):
     search.google.com/search-console → Settings → Users and permissions
     → Add user → paste SA email → Restricted/Full as needed.
     (Service accounts must be added to EACH property separately.)

   GTM (Tag Manager):
     tagmanager.google.com → User Management → +
     → paste SA email → choose Account permissions (Read or higher)
     → choose Container permissions (Read for read-only access).

Once dropped here, the broker auto-detects it on startup
(GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS is set internally) and the GA4 / GSC / GTM
endpoints become available. Verify with: curl $BROKER_URL/health
